  "final_text": "\"Start a debug session\" maps to `stm32 debug start`. ELF will be autodiscovered from `stm32-project.jsonc` if present in the working tree.\nThe debug session failed to start. Here's the diagnosis:\n\n---\n\n**Error: ST-LINK firmware upgrade required**\n\nThe gdbserver (v7.13.0) connected to your ST-LINK probe but exited immediately with exit code 6 because the probe's firmware is too old to be used by this version of the GDB server.\n\n**What to do:**\n\n1. **Upgrade your ST-LINK firmware** using the ST-LINK Upgrade Utility:\n   - Open **STM32CubeProgrammer** \u2192 Connect your probe \u2192 go to **Firmware upgrade** (top-right icon) \u2192 click **Upgrade**\n   - Or run: `STM32_Programmer_CLI --upgrade-st-link`\n\n2. Once upgraded, re-run the debug session:\n   ```\n   stm32 debug start\n   ```\n\n> **Note:** This is consistent with the known bench F401RE issue (ST-Link V2J28M17 emitting `DEV_USB_COMM_ERR`/firmware errors). After the firmware upgrade that board's probe should work normally."
}